Given an array of size n, write a program to find the second largest number in the array.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer n, the size of the array.

The second line contains n integers, representing the elements of the array.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

Print a single integer, the second largest number in the array.

Sample Input 0

5
1 3 5 2 4
Sample Output 0

4
Sample Input 1

6
10 20 20 8 6 15
Sample Output 1

15
Explanation 1

The second largest number is 8 (should not consider duplicates).

Sample Input 2

6
10 10 10 10 10 10
Sample Output 2

No second largest number



import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
       Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
       int n=sc.nextInt();
       int arr[]=new int [n];
       for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
       {
        arr[i]=sc.nextInt();
       }
       
       int m=arr[0];
       for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
       {
        if(arr[i]>m)
        m=arr[i];
       }
       
       int t=arr[0];
       for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
       {
        if(arr[i]>t && arr[i]<m)
        {
            t=arr[i];
        } 
       }
       if(t!=m)
       {System.out.print(t);
       return;}
       else
       System.out.print("No second largest number");
    }
}
